<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3209] Memory codec</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3209</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;This codec stores all terms/postings in RAM.  It uses an&lt;br/&gt;
FST&amp;lt;BytesRef&amp;gt;.  This is useful on a primary key field to ensure&lt;br/&gt;
lookups don&apos;t need to hit disk, to keep NRT reopen time fast even&lt;br/&gt;
under IO contention.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
