                                                    <comments>
                    <comment id="13050791" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 00:11:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch; I think it&apos;s working and ready to commit.  All tests pass w/ it, and I went and disabled the same tests that avoid SimpleText codec.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13050793" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 00:13:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;To clarify: this codec stores postings on disk, but then on read (for searching) it loads the full byte[] from disk into RAM.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13050909" author="simonw" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 07:48:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3069&quot; title=&quot;Lucene should have an entirely memory resident term dictionary&quot;&gt;LUCENE-3069&lt;/a&gt; right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13050912" author="dweiss" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 08:00:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like a related thing to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13051002" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 12:52:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Woops!  I forgot about &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3069&quot; title=&quot;Lucene should have an entirely memory resident term dictionary&quot;&gt;LUCENE-3069&lt;/a&gt;, but, yes this is very similar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But I think one difference is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3069&quot; title=&quot;Lucene should have an entirely memory resident term dictionary&quot;&gt;LUCENE-3069&lt;/a&gt; aims to have all terms memory resident but postings would still reside in the Directory, I think?  Whereas my patch here puts all terms and postings in RAM (in a single FST).  The postings format is similar to what PulsingCodec does, ie, doc + tf + pos + payload are all serialized into a single byte[] using delta vInts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I think we should keep &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3069&quot; title=&quot;Lucene should have an entirely memory resident term dictionary&quot;&gt;LUCENE-3069&lt;/a&gt; open, as an enhancement to this codec to make it separately controllable whether postings should also be in RAM?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
